description:
Contract test for the FlywheelServer JSON API shapes.

## /snapshot GET shape
Top-level fields: generatedAt (ISO 8601 string), server (object), ssh (object),
  agents (array), beads (object | null), vpsHealth (object | null), mail (object),
  actions (array of action names), lastError (string | undefined)
server: { host, port, sessionName, remoteProjectPath? }
ssh: { connected (boolean), host? (string) }
beads (when non-null): { total, open, inProgress, closed, blocked, velocityPerHour?, etaHours? }

## /action POST response envelope
Success: { ok: true, action: string, payload: unknown }
Error 400: { ok: false, error: string }
Error 500: { ok: false, error: string }
Oversized body (> 256 KB): connection reset or 413 status

## WebSocket action_result message
{ type: 'action_result', ok: true, action: string, payload: unknown }

## DashboardSnapshot snapshot_push message
{ type: 'snapshot', ...DashboardSnapshot }

## Test setup
Start a real FlywheelServer with no SSH (SSH offline mode), hit /snapshot,
assert shape. Send invalid JSON to /action, assert 400. Send body > 256 KB, assert size-limit behaviour.

File: test/e2e/setup.ts

Create a shared E2E harness:

interface E2EResult {
  exitCode: number;
  stdout: string;
  stderr: string;
  durationMs: number;
}

async function runFlywheel(args: string[], opts?: { stdin?: string; env?: Record<string,string> }): Promise<E2EResult>
- spawns: node dist/cli.js ...args
- captures stdout, stderr, exit code, duration
- logs EVERYTHING before returning:
  [E2E] cmd: flywheel {args}
  [E2E] exit: {exitCode} in {durationMs}ms
  [E2E] stdout: {full stdout}
  [E2E] stderr: {full stderr}

skipIfNoSsh(): skips test if ~/.flywheel/ssh.yaml is missing (vitest.skipIf)
getTestProject(): returns FLYWHEEL_TEST_PROJECT env var or 'flywheel-e2e-{timestamp}'
cleanupTestProject(name): SSHs to VPS and removes the test project dir

This harness ensures every E2E test has full, detailed output for debugging CI failures.

Acceptance: harness logs every CLI invocation with full I/O; no test silently skips output
